Here’s an example using `data-*` attributes for event handling:

jsx
function ListComponent({ items }) {
  const handleClick = (e) => {
    const id = e.currentTarget.dataset.id;
    console.log("Clicked item:", id);
  };

  return (
    <div>
      {items.map((item) => (
        <button 
          key={item.id} 
          data-id={item.id} 
          onClick={handleClick}
        >
          {item.name}
        </button>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

The `data-id` attribute stores the item ID, which is retrieved in the `handleClick` function using `e.currentTarget.dataset.id`.
